[h1]ElderGPT Spirit Ring[/h1]
[i]A read-only AI advisor overlay for Ascend From Nine Mountains.[/i]

Want advice without tabbing out to a browser?
ElderGPT Spirit Ring reads your live game state through the official modAPI, builds a compact context snapshot, and lets you chat with the AI model of your choice inside the game.

[h2]Highlights[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Read-only by design[/b] - it does not automate combat, spend resources, or make choices for you.
[*][b]Always nearby[/b] - open it from the floating Spirit Ring button, or from the combat victory screen.
[*][b]Live context[/b] - advice is grounded in your current run, not a generic wiki answer.
[*][b]Deep game knowledge[/b] - the AI is fed relevant crafting, combat, and cultivation knowledge based on what you are doing right now.
[*][b]Persistent chat with sessions[/b] - conversations are saved automatically. Switch between chats, start new ones, or pick up where you left off.
[*][b]Smart context management[/b] - automatically detects your model's context window and compacts long conversations so the AI never loses track.
[*][b]Streaming responses[/b] - see words as the AI responds, with markdown formatting and a loading animation.
[*][b]Optional proactive hints[/b] - it can chime in after important moments like combat, travel, crafting, and time skips.
[*][b]Bring your own model[/b] - works with OpenAI-compatible providers, Anthropic API endpoints, or local servers.
[*][b]Configurable timeout[/b] - increase the request timeout up to 999 seconds for slow or distributed inference setups.
[*][b]Customizable UI[/b] - adjust text size, window size, and drag the panel anywhere on screen. Position persists across sessions.
[/list]

[h2]What you can ask it[/h2]
[quote]
"What should I focus on next?"

"How should I approach this fight?"

"Is this a good time to travel?"

"What am I missing in this crafting setup?"

"Which stats or resources are holding me back?"

"Explain how Inscribed Patterns harmony works."
[/quote]

[h2]Quick start[/h2]
[list]
[*]Open the Spirit Ring from the floating circular button.
[*]Open [b]Settings[/b].
[*]Enter your API URL, API key, and model ID.
[*]Pick a persona if you want.
[*]Ask for advice normally in plain language.
[/list]

[h2]Personas[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Elder[/b] - An ancient cultivation elder who speaks in Xianxia idioms. Gives advice framed through Dao philosophy while referencing actual game mechanics.
[*][b]Calculator[/b] - A cold optimization engine. Leads with numbers, percentages, and comparisons. No fluff.
[*][b]Custom[/b] - Write your own persona prompt. The AI still receives live game state and knowledge context.
[/list]

[h2]Recommended AI setup options[/h2]
[b]1) Use your favorite hosted provider[/b]

If you already have a provider you like, use that.
[url=https://openrouter.ai/docs/quickstart]OpenRouter[/url] is an easy choice because it gives you access to a lot of models through one OpenAI-compatible endpoint.

[code]https://openrouter.ai/api/v1[/code]

[b]2) Good free hosted option: NVIDIA NIM[/b]

[url=https://build.nvidia.com]NVIDIA NIM[/url] is a strong free option for testing and light use through the NVIDIA Developer Program.
It exposes an OpenAI-compatible API, so it drops straight into the mod.

[code]https://integrate.api.nvidia.com/v1[/code]

If you want a fast, strong default there, try [url=https://docs.api.nvidia.com/nim/reference/moonshotai-kimi-k2-instruct-0905]moonshotai / kimi-k2-instruct-0905[/url].
It is one of the faster good options on NIM right now and usually feels responsive for in-game advice.

[b]3) Good free local option: run your own server[/b]

If you want private or fully local inference, run an OpenAI-compatible server with [url=https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp]llama.cpp[/url] or [url=https://github.com/LostRuins/koboldcpp]KoboldCpp[/url].

Good small local model families to try:
[list]
[*][url=https://developers.googleblog.com/bring-state-of-the-art-agentic-skills-to-the-edge-with-gemma-4/]Gemma 4[/url] small variants
[*]Qwen 3.5 small variants / GGUF builds
[/list]

If your local runner exposes an OpenAI-compatible [code]/v1[/code] endpoint, ElderGPT Spirit Ring can use it.

[h2]Good to know[/h2]
[list]
[*]This mod does not include an API key or a bundled model.
[*]Advice quality depends heavily on the model you choose.
[*]Faster models usually feel better for moment-to-moment gameplay.
[*]The mod auto-detects your model's context window and output limits when possible, but you can override them in Settings.
[*]Long conversations are automatically summarized to stay within context limits.
[*]Proactive hints are optional and can be disabled in Settings.
[/list]

[h2]Feedback and bugs[/h2]
If the advice feels wrong, confusing, or out of date, leave a comment with what was happening in-game and what the mod told you.
That is the fastest way to improve it.

